Update to the solutions by @johnfn and @WilliamChelman due to new syntax for tasks.json, and capability of using npm instead of native shell.

If you have a check-types script in package.json:
```json
{
  "scripts":  {
    "check-types": "tsc -w --noEmit"
  }
}
```

You can add the following task to your tasks.json (note if you don't already have a tasks.json, it goes in the root folder/.vscode/tasks.json): 
```json
{
  "version": "2.0.0",
  "tasks": [
    {
      "label": "check types",
      "detail": "Get all typescript errors in problems pane",
      "script": "check-types",
      "type": "npm",
      "isBackground": true,
      "problemMatcher": "$tsc-watch",
      "presentation": {
        "reveal": "silent"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

Now you can run this task any time you want project-wide type error checking in the problems pane rather than just in open files.

